Business Brief -- Dycom Industries Inc.:
   Telecommunications Concern
   Is Sued by Former President
Mr. Stover alleges that Dycom at one point improperly made
a $5 million adjustment to sales of its subsidiaries, thereby
inflating subsequent financial statements. Mr. Stover also
alleges that, as part of his dismissal at Dycom, he was
suspended illegally from his position as president of Ansco,
now a subsidiary of Dycom. The suit seeks unspecified
damages.
   Dycom's chief executive officer, Thomas Pledger said any
charges in the suit "as they pertain to me are unfounded."
Otherwise, he declined to comment on the litigation.